SIMPLE: liberality
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liberality
<hw>Lib`er*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(-⟦acr⟧l"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Liberalities</plw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L. <ets>liberalitas</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>lib⟦eacute⟧ralit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality
or state of being liberal; liberal disposition or practice; freedom from
narrowness or prejudice; generosity; candor; charity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>liberality</qex> is but cast away⟦br⟧
Which makes us borrow what we can not pay.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A gift; a gratuity; -- sometimes in the plural;
<as>as, a prudent man is not impoverished by his
<ex>liberalities</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liberalization</ent>⟦br⟧
